                <h2>Be Suspicious</h2>
                <p>Never open email attachments or links unless you're expecting them, even if the email seems to come from someone you know. Phishing often uses infected files to install malware.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-4">
                <h1>Tip: #3</h1>
                <h2>Verify the Sender</h2>
                <p>If you're unsure about an email, verify the sender by contacting them through official channels (don't use the contact information from the email).</p>
